.TH "cpuidle_register_driver" 9 "cpuidle_register_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_register_driver \- registers a driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cpuidle_register_driver
.BI "(struct cpuidle_driver *drv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
a pointer to a valid struct cpuidle_driver
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register the driver under a lock to prevent concurrent attempts to
[un]register the driver from occuring at the same time.

Returns 0 on success, a negative error code (returned by
\fB__cpuidle_register_driver\fP) otherwise.
